<item>
            <title>[SOLR-7522] Implement single-valued faceting on numeric fields</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-7522</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The underlying issue is &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-7521&quot; title=&quot;Allow indexed numeric field to be retrieved as string index.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-7521&quot;&gt;SOLR-7521&lt;/a&gt;, a Lucene 5 bug / &quot;feature&quot; that prevents a string index view of an indexed numeric field.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue will address &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-7496&quot; title=&quot;Empty buckets when faceting with JSON API over EnumField and TrieIntField&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-7496&quot;&gt;SOLR-7496&lt;/a&gt; for single valued numeric fields.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
